FBIS4-12704 "drnes070_n_94008" FBIS-NES-94-070 Daily Report 11 Apr 1994 LEBANON Palestinian Gunmen Said To Kill Fatah Official Palestinian Gunmen Said To Kill Fatah Official NC1104140994 Paris AFP in English 1343 GMT 11 Apr 94 NC1104140994 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Sidon, Lebanon, April 11 (AFP) -- Palestinian gunmen shot dead an official of PLO chief Yasir 'Arafat's Fatah movement on Monday [11 April] in southern Lebanon, Palestinian sources said. Husayn Abu-Zayd, 47, a deputy to Fatah's former intelligence chief in Lebanon Kamal Midhat, was killed with automatic weapons in the 'Ayn al-Hulwah Palestinian refugee camp on the eastern outskirts of this port city, they said. His killers, two brothers who also belong to Fatah, were arrested by Palestinian military police and handed over to the Lebanese authorities, they said. An informed Palestinian sources said Abu-Zayd had had a financial and personal dispute with the two men.
